The article discusses the partnerships and collaborations between the United States and countries in the Americas in various areas such as economic trade and commerce, citizen security, education and innovation, energy and climate, and defense cooperation. The United States aims to enhance its leadership in Latin America and recognizes the region's emerging markets as key players in the global economy. Efforts are being made to strengthen trade agreements and economic engagement with Latin American countries. In terms of citizen security, the United States is committed to creating practical partnerships to address insecurity and violent crime in the region. Education and innovation are seen as important for progress, and initiatives have been launched to foster educational exchanges and enhance the connection between education and innovation. The Energy and Climate Partnership of the Americas (ECPA) aims to advance clean energy technologies and combat climate change. Defense cooperation is also emphasized, with the United States promoting equal partnerships and collective action to address transnational security challenges in the Americas.